cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.DS 

The paper discusses differentiable optimization algorithms for combinatorial problems, which are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of differentiable optimization is particularly relevant to machine learning, which is why cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses applications in sequence-to-sequence modeling (cs.CL, Computational Linguistics) and image classification (cs.CV, Computer Vision), which further support these categories. Finally, the paper discusses linear programming, which is a fundamental topic in computer science and optimization (cs.DS, Data Structures and Algorithms).
